<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 5:51AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...WIDESPREAD FOG AFFECTING THE REGION...
Surface observations indicate that widespread fog is affecting
Deep South Texas and the Rio Grande Valley at this time. The fog
will generally reduce visibilities to between 1 and 3 miles.
Isolated more dense fog, with visibilities reduced to less than 1
mile, are likely.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights,
and avoid following other cars too closely in the fog from now
until the mid-morning hours of today.</description>
